The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, February 19, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, February 19, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	From Howrah and Sealdah to Shramik Bhavan, AJC Bose Road, at 1 pm. West Bengal Security and Co-Workers Union members will converge for a protest meet.				 																Fun fair				 																																	An interactive fun fair for children at Kangaroo Kids School, New Alipore, from 9 am to 4 pm. Pottery-making, art and craft and gardening will be taught. 				 																Cable show				 																																	Cable TV Show 2004 will be inaugurated at Netaji Indoor Stadium, 10.45 am.				 																Hard Talk				 																																	Alapan Bandopadhyay, chief executive officer of CMDA, will meet readers of The Telegraph at the CMDA office conference room in Salt Lake, 5.30 pm.				 																Folk art				 																																	An exhibition-cum-sale of innovative and traditional works of women patuas of Midnapore at Madhusudan Mancha, from 2 pm to 8 pm.				 																Pen skills				 																																	A short course on dramatic writing, organised by Indian Institute of Cerebral Palsy in collaboration with British Council, at the Taratala institute from 10 am to 4 pm.				 																Exhibitions				 																																	An exhibition of water colours by Paresh Maity on view at CIMA Gallery, from 2 pm to 7 pm.				 																																	Images and Imagination, an exhibition of the works of eight artists from India and abroad, will be inaugurated at Galerie 88 at 6 pm.
